@node SS_Intro "SeaShell/Intro"
@prev main
@next SS_Requirements
@TOC main

            @{b}Introduction@{ub}

   @{b}SeaShell@{ub} is a simple front-end to introduce values needed to create a file
   for @{" Shelly " link SS_Shelly}. At the moment, @{b}SeaShell@{ub} allows user to
   introduce all necessary parameters simply moving mouse on the necessary 
   gadget and clicking to insert values (see @{" Usage " link SS_Usage} for more informations). 

   The demo version available on Aminet is a complete version with an annoying 
   requester appearing everytime you try to save a file.
   However, you cannot receive upgrades till you will pay the required quote.
   At the moment version 1.2 is quite finished and it includes new features 
   like:

	- On-line documentation/help
	- Tooltypes reading to properly set directories in which
	  SeaShell will search help file and more.
        - Possibility to insert Arexx commands using a string requester.
	- Localization (program will be provided with two catalogs:
	  english and italian)

@endnode
@node SS_Requirements "SeaShell/Requirements"
@prev SS_Intro
@next SS_Installation
@TOC main

            @{b}Requirements@{ub}

   @{b}SeaShell@{ub} requires:

   - an Amiga with at least 512K -8)
   - kickstart 2.04 or above
   - gadtools.library,reqtools.library,asl.library

@endnode
@node SS_Installation "SeaShell/Installation"

            @{b}Installation@{ub}

   To install @{b}SeaShell@{ub} you have to copy all files in the desired
   directory or click. 

@endnode
@node SS_Usage "SeaShell/Usage"
@prev SS_Installation
@next SS_Arexx
@TOC main

            @{b}Usage@{ub}

   @{b}SeaShell@{ub} is very simple to use. Some options can be selected both
   from menu, others by clicking appropriate gadgets. Now, some explanations 
   about the main menu.

   @{b}Project Menu@{ub} allow user to Load an old file, saving the current file
   and creating a new one. The same menu provides you others item such as
   Print,About and Quit.

   NEW  - Resets all string gadgets. Now you can edit a new file. Note that
       if the current file has not been saved and you select this option, a 
       request will appear asking if you want to save the file. 
  
   LOAD - Opens a file requester to select an old file to load. For default, will be
       shown all files with extension equal to ".shy", the standard extension
                 for Shelly files.

   SAVE AS - Opens a file requester to select a filename to save the current file
  
   SAVE - Saves current file. The current file will be saved everytime a value
          has been changed since the last saving.

   PRINT - Prints current file.

   ABOUT - Opens an about window

   QUIT - Quits SeaShell


   The @{b}Main@{ub} window includes four gadgets named:

      EDIT  - it opens editing windows
      ABOUT - showing an about window
      QUIT  - quitting from program

   The @{b}Edit@{ub} window presents some string gadgets corresponding at some
   Shelly parameters plus a cycle gadget to select an appropriate mode for the
   object, a cycle gadget to select the output format and a checkbox to set
   the RENDER condition. This option is valid only if you selected POV as valid
   output format, because RENDER allows Shelly set as true a valid POV flag for
   preview image.

   Last version of Shelly supports these output formats:

      - POV (Persistance of Vision)
      - RPL (Real 3D)
      - T3D (Imagine)
      - RAW (pure binary format)
      - X3D (for 3D glasses)

   The @{b}Nodules@{ub} window is used to set others Shelly values, expecially all
   those regarding shell's nodules. Note that final result will depend also on
   some flag such as: NODULE,NORMAL & NEWNODE. 
   You can select one of these modes using the cycle gadget in the Params window.

   For more informations about Shelly parameters, look for the official Shelly
   documentation distributed with Shelly (Aminet gfx/3dobj). 

@endnode
@node SS_Arexx "SeaShell/Arexx commands"
@prev SS_Usage
@next SS_History

            @{b}Arexx commands@{ub}

	@{b}SeaShell@{ub} opens an Arexx port called SEASHELLREXX. At the
	moment, the program is able to parse these internal commands (actually 9):

	Command	  : @{b}About@{ub}
	Syntax    : @{b}ABOUT@{ub} 
        Info      : Shows the about requester
	Parameters: Nothing

	Command	  : @{b}Copy@{ub}
	Syntax    : @{b}COPY src_gad dest_gad@{ub}
	Info      : It accepts two parameters being the source gadget
		    and the destination gadget. Available gadgets can be
		    viewed at the end of this chapter.
	Parameters: Source and destination gadgets. 

                    @{i}Ex. COPY P1 ALPHA /* It copies string inside gadget P1
			                 to  gadget ALPHA */@{ui}


	Command	  : @{b}Erase{ub}
	Syntax    : @{b}ERASE src_gad@{ub}
	Info      : It clears the gadget. Default value is the BLANK char.  
	Parameters: Gadget to clear.

		    @{i}Ex. ERASE P1 /* P1 setted to " " */@{ui}
	
        Command   : @{b}Eraseall@{ub}
	Syntax    : @{b}ERASEALL@{ub}
	Info	  : Same as above but all gadgets are affected.
	Parameters: Nothing.

	Command	  : @{b}Loadfile@{ub}
	Syntax    : @{b}LOADFILE@{ub}
	Info	  : It opens the file requester to select a file to load.
	Parameters: Nothing

	Command   : @{b}Print@{ub}
	Syntax    : @{b}PRINT@{ub}
        Info      : Send to printer current values
        Parameters: None

	Command   : @{b}Saveas@{ub}
	Syntax    : @{b}SAVEAS@{ub}
	Info	  : It opens the file requester to select a name for the project 
		    to save. For more information about its usage, see
		    chapter @{"Usage" link SS_Usage}.
	Parameters: Nothing.

	Command	  : @{b}Save@{ub}
	Syntax    : @{b}SAVE@{ub}
	Info	  : It saves the current project.
	Parameters: Nothing.

	Command   : @{b}Setvalue@{ub}
	Syntax    : @{b}SETVALUE src_gad value@{ub}
	Info	  : It sets the value of gadget src_gad to "value" 
	Parameters: src_gad - GadgetID
		    value   - Value to assign

		   @{i}Ex. SETVALUE ALPHA 0.678@{ui}

	Command   : @{b}Quit@{ub}
	Syntax    : @{b}QUIT@{ub}
	Info	  : Abandoning the program.
	Parameters: Nothing.

	Some examples of Arexx scripts are distributed with @{b}SeaShell@{ub}.
        They can be launched after main program execution.

        			@{b}WARNING!@{ub}

	A problem actually exists. When you write an Arexx script for
	@{b}SeaShell@{ub}, be sure that no more than one blank occours 
        between the command name and the first parameter.Same thing for
        commands requiring two parameters: max one blank is allowed between
        the first and the second parameter.

				@{b}Parameters list (gadgets)@{ub}

        Every gadget is associated at a parameter. These are parameters that
        can be actually edited using SeaShell:

	@{b}Nodules@{ub} category:

	@{i}P1,P2,P3,W1,W2,W12,W22,W13,W23,L1,L2,L3,Off2,Off3@{ui}

	Other parameters:
	
	@{i}Alpha,beta,ph,omega,my,smin,smax,sd,omin,omax,od,a,b@{ui}

	Two cycle gadgets are used to select parameters like:

	@{i}mode@{ui}   - choice has to be done selecting  NORMAL,NODULE,NEWNODE
	@{i}format@{ui} - output format selection: RPL,POV,T3D,RAW,X3D

        Last parameter can be set to true or false clicking on the boolean
        gadget:

	@{i}render@{ui} - it can be TRUE o FALSE

	To properly set this gadget use @{b}SETVALUE@{ub} so:

	@{i}Ex. SETVALUE RENDER [TRUE or FALSE]@{ui} 



@endnode
